            "creation_date": 1542967785,
            "body": "<p>This is the Maven Repository index, used for suggesting Dependencies and Plugins when you're adding some to your project. And yes, it's quite normal to be this big, Maven Central contains <em>a lot<\/em> of content.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can delete the file, but it will be downloaded again unless you disable the indexing:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Mmtz6.png\" alt=\"preferences screenshot\"><\/p>\n\n<p>You can also micromanage the indexes for your various repositories if you go to <code>Window<\/code> -> <code>Show View<\/code> -> <code>Other...<\/code> -> <code>Maven<\/code> -> <code>Maven Repositories<\/code>, and right-click any of your repos:<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/Ryjzt.png\" alt=\"Maven Repositories screenshot\"><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 53444616,
            "question_id": 53442737
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9a1274c02acc623b1a09d3639261dfa7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 4220083,
